Arrange grahams in even layer on bottom of 13x9-inch pan, cutting to fit if necessary; set aside. Beat cream cheese in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until creamy. Gradually add milk, mixing until well blended. Add dry pudding mix; beat 1 minute. Fold in half of the whipped topping. Spread over grahams in pan; cover with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight. Sprinkle with coconut. Cut into squares to serve. Garnish with fresh berries just before serving, if desired. Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.